gham,\n1214 East 941 h Street,\nBrooklyn, New York.\nYou are hereby required to ap\npear to the Lilt of Complaint in the\nabove styled cause u or before I lie\n131 h day of March, Al. 1949. other\nwise the allegations therein will l>*\ntoken as confessed.\nThis Order is to he published\nonce a Week for four eopsecutive\nweeks In Th Key West Citizen, a\nnewspaper published at Key Wesi,\nMonroe County, Florida,\nDONE and ORDERED Hits I Jilt\nday of February, A. 1/. 1849.\nEARL It ada\u00dfm,\nClark of (tie Circuit Court,\nMonroe County, Florida\nBy (sd) Florence e. Sawyer,\nDeputy Clerk.\n(Seat)\nJ. Y Porter IV,\nSolicitor for Plaintiff\nfeh. I 4 21 2.3: mar. 7,1949.\nROBERTS OFFICE SUPPLIES\nand EQUIPMENT\n128 DUVAL iT. PHONE 250\nRoyal Standard and Portable\nTYPEWRITERS\nAllan Woles Adding Mochlnos\nRemington Adding Moehinot\nPortable Moileln I OvlH)\ntil\nUm Our Installment Plan _\nLEGALS\nNOTICE OF INTENTION TO MAKE\nAPPLICATION FOR FINAL\nDISCHARGE\n(Probate\nIN COI HT OE THE (II \\TV*\nJUDGE, MONROE COUN TV .5\nSTATE OE FLORIDA. IN !*l{(-\nBATE.\nIn re the Estate of\nMINNIE B. COX, Deceased.\nTo All Whom it May Concern:\nNotice is hereby given that Harry.*-\nR. Saunders filed his final report a:C\nExecutor of the estate of Minnie B.\nCox, deceased: that he filed his\npetition for final discharge, and\nthat he will apply to the Honorable\nRaymond R. Lord, County Judge of\nMonroe County, Florida, on the 24th\nday of March, 1949, for approval of}\nsame and for final discharge as]\nExecutor of the estate of Minnie B,:\nCox, deceased.\nivated this 21st day of February, i'\n1949. l\n(s) HARRY R. SAUNDERS, j\nExecutor of the estate of\nMinnie B Cox deceased.\nfeb.2l-28; mar.'-J 4,1949\nIN THE CIRCUIT COURT OF THE;\nELEVENTH JIDICIAL CIHCI IT j\nOE THE STATE OE FLORIDA, j\nIN AND FOR MONROE COUNTY.\nIN CHANCERY.\nCase Vo. IMM.\nANNE WICKS ORR.\nPlaintiff, i\nvs. DIVORCE.\nNATHANIEL A ORR.\nI >cfendant.\nNOTICE TO APPEAR\nIN\u2019 THE NAME OF THE STATE 1\nOF FLORIDA\nTO: Nathaniel A. Orr,\ne/O New England Telephone\nand Telegraph Company,\nLaconia, New Hampshire\nYou are hereby ordered and re-\nqnireil to file vour Appearance on\nthe mil day of March, A. D. 1949\nin the above styled cause, now j\npending in the Circuit Court of th*-\nEleventh Judicial Circuit of th\u00df*j\nState of Florida, in and for Mon fop\nCounty, in Chancery, wherein Anne i\nWicks >rr is plaintiff and you atv\ndefendant, wherein said plaintiff\nseeks a divorce, and in defaultxf\nsuch Appearance a Decree Pro Coy\nfesso will be entered against you.\nIt is further ordered that Ibis\u2019\norder be published,\u2019once U week for J\nfour (4) consecutive weeks in The i\nKey West Citizen, a newspaper of j\ngeneral circulation published \u2022Ui i\nMonroe Cttpnly, Fbtr.ida. I\nDone ami Ordered at Key West.\nMonroe. County, Florida, this !2ih\ndav of February, A. 1. 1949. j\nEARL It. ADAMS. j\nClerk of the Circuit Court',.\nMonroe County, Florida.\nBy (sd) Florence E. Sawyer,\nDeputy Clerk.\n(Circuit Court Seal)\nW. CUR It V HARRIS.\nSolicitor for Plaintiff\nfelt. 14-21-23: vnar.7,1949.\nDrive it and learn why\nIts the Car that's\n103 ways different/\n1 aaMmpjfc; Behind the wheel of a Frazer you suddenly realize you see much\nbetter, drive much easier. All other cars become old-fashioned\nDiscover the balanced car. The Frazer has amazing new distnbu\nt\u2019on mass antl load* Its inner-spring front, shocks and triple-control\nsteering are basic and major improvements in engineering.\nThe differences of the Frazer begin with \u201cyears ahead\u201d driving ease.\nriding comfort and luxury. You have air-conditioned coolness or\nwarmth. You have the widest choice of colors and fabrics ever avail-\neconomy which only the Frazer\u2019s high compression engine can gu.e.\nYou have a whole world of differences |to discover in the Frazer\u2014\nfeHliignSnp'- See it. at your nearest Kaiser-Frazer dealer\u2019s\u2014today!\nflfli! Hint! Hear! CUa&t\\ U/'<>'.clu(C Every Suriajr.. sa~e b'-p. cjbc.i!\n_ _\\gr Nj, v M\nEASTERN AUTO HOME\nE. E. Price Motors, Dist. Whidden Motor Sales, Inc. Garrison Motor Sales, Inc. Gautier Motor Sales\n1785 S.W. Bih St.. Miami. Fla. Coral Gables. Fla. Fort Myers. Fie. Homestead. Fla.\nLowy\u2019s Motor Sales Tropical Motor Car Cos., Inc. Lawson Motors Wallace Motors, Inc\nMiami Beach. Fla. Fort Lauderdale. Fla. Delray Beach, Fie. West Palm Beach. Fla,\nSugarland Motora V-M Motors\nClewiston, Fla. Hollywood. Fie.\n\u25a0ML IT--\nHER SECRET STAR\nBtf Bennie G.cMtUl\nAf NtwtUat*\"*\nChapter 23\nHE WANTED very much to be\nfair with Millicent, to do the\nright thing. He had loved her\ndeeply in the beginning; mar\nriage, to him, had been a sacred\nthing. How was he to know that\nthis wasn\u2019t just another one of\nher selfish whims?\nMillicent was spoiled and self\nish, and too rich for her own\ngood. A sick patient meant noth\ning to-her if she wanted to go\ndancing.\nIf he refused, there was the\ndevil to pay. In order to avoid\nsuch scenes he had almost de\nstroyed his reputation in his own\ncommunity. Millicent had no con\nception of what it meant to be a\ndoctor\u2019s wife. Nor had she any\nunderstanding of a man who re\nfused to live on his wife\u2019s bounty.\nHe must be fair, however. He\nmust remember that once he had\nloved Millicent enough to marry\nher. Perhaps he had expected too\nmuch of her. It would take an\nextraordinary woman to put up\nwith a doctor\u2019s irregular hours\nand his inability to live his own\nlife like ordinary men. He must\nremember that in his forthcom\ning interview with Millicent.\nHe consulted his wrist-watch,\nsuddenly aware that time was\npassing. It was six o\u2019clock. Milli\ncent had said she would be there\nat five-thirty, but she had never\nbeen on time in her gay, careless\nlife. Time, to her, meant nothing,\nalthough she had vowted she was\nturning over anew leaf.\nIt was a quarter after six when\nshe arrived, breathless and on a\nwhiff of expensive perfume. She\nwas a pretty, dark-haired girl\nwith alert black eyes and rather\nfull, petulant lips.\nShe sat down in the chair\nwhich George Newton offered her,\nsaying in a sweet voice:\n\u201cIt\u2019s a cute town.\u201d She flashed\nher most winsome smile. \u201cI never\nrealized it before, but of course\nI\u2019ve always driven right through\non the way to the cape. Never\npaid much attention to the vil\nlages along the way.\u201d\n\u201cYes, Carrolton s a fine place.\nHe nodded and, unconsciously,\nthrew his chest out a little. \u201cIt s.\ngot just about everything\u2014good\nschools, a fairly adequate hos\npital, churches\n\u201cAnd a wide-awake Chamber\nof Commerce, of which you are\nan active member.\u201d She laughed\nand waggled a playful forefinger.\n\u201cI can see that. You\u2019ve got a\ndarling little movie house, too.\nWould you believe it\u2014l went to\na movie while I was waiting for\nit to be five-thirty. That\u2019s why I\nwas late, dear. I hope you\u2019re not\ntoo peeved with me.\u201d She paused\nto pout prettily and to work on\nhim with her eyes.\nHe looked away from her and\npretended to rearrange the pa\npers on the desk behind which\nhe had seated himself. \u201cNo, I\u2019m\nnot peeved. I said it was all right.\nI said I wasn\u2019t very busy this\nafternoon.\u201d\n\u201cWhy, that\u2019s wonderful! I\nhadn\u2019t expected such luck!\u201d\nAs she spoke she clapped her\nsmall palms together in delight,\nand George all but groaned\naloud. Millicent hadn\u2019t changed\none single bit, he reflected, in\nspite of her avowal that she\u2019d\nturned over anew leaf. Hardly a\nsecond had passed before she was\nsaying in that gay, exuberant\nvoice he knew so well:\n\u201cThen we can go places and\nhave fun, like we used to. We\ncould drive into'Boston and have\na late dinner, and go dancing.\u201d\nShe paused, as if realizing she\nwas going too far. Before he could\nsay anything, she was rattling on:\n\u201cOr maybe we could eat right\nhere in this quaint town. I\u2019m sure\nyou must have a good restaurant\nalong with your good schools and\nchurches and things. As I said be\nfore, the movie house was really\na darling, although the picture\nwas a little on the oldish side.\u201d\n\u201cI can\u2019t understand that,\u201d\nGeorge said, without thinking.\nMONDAY, FEBRUARY 23. I**49\nWe usually get the same picture*\nthey have in Boston. 1\nHe flushed, annoyed with him*\nself. Why did he fee! impelled to\ndefend Carrolton to this scatter\nbrain whorp he had once fancied\nhimself in love with? Why dnt\nshe go on back to Bodon where\nshe belonged? What wa* tie point\nin discussing a reconciliation that\ncouldn\u2019t possibly work out?\nMillicent turning the conver\nsation back to where she wanted\nit, said \u201cI\u2019m sure you have a v* rv\nnice restaurant in this darling\ntown. Some nice,\nwhere we can sit as long wa\nwant to and talk.\u201d\nShe paused, but only tn uet her\nbreath and anew start. \u201cI'll ad\nmit I haven't been able to find\nsuch a place. I\u2019ve been eating al\nthe hotel and \u2014well, I don t want\nto hurt your feelings, dear, but\nthe service is ghastly. Something\nshould be done about it. But I in\nsure you must have a nice te.stau\nrant. It\u2019s probably in somebody\nhouse. We really should patH.m/e\nit, now that you live here. Bight,\ndear?\u201d\n\u201cYes. We have a restaurant.\"\nThere was an edge to George's\nvoice. \u201cIt\u2019s not in anybody's\nhouse. It's right on the main\nstreet just like everything else.\nAcross from the hotel. Can't see\nhow you missed it.\n\u201cOh, that. I thought it was a\npool room. Sorry, dear. I didn't\nmean to belittle. I'm sure it\u2019s\nquite roomy and charming on the\ninside.\u201d\n\u201cIt\u2019s adequate. Most people in\nCarrolton eat at home. a> they\nshould. And don't ask where\u2019s the\norchestra and the da rice floor.\nThere\u2019s only a juke box and no\nspace for dancing. People go\nthere to eat. Sounds odd, doesn't\nit? But that\u2019s what restaurants\nare for.\u201d\nAs he spoke he put on his top\ncoat and picked up his hat\n\u201cReady, Millicent?\u201d He did not\nadd, \u201cCome on; let\u2019s get it over\nwith,\u201d although he wanted to.\n(To be continued)","height":"24351","width":"19110"}}
